cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD

This paper discusses the impact of science and recent developments in impact measurements, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on bibliometric results and evaluation of research suggests that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category. The discussion of impact on society and the effects of impact measurements on the science system suggest cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as likely sub-categories. The discussion of measuring impact and problems associated with impact measurement suggest cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) as possible sub-categories.
